    "4010310": {
        "Desc": "Talk to Kaveh",
        "Step": "After a chaotic skirmish, it was Kaveh who claimed the diadem. But something seems wrong...",
        "Talk": [
            [
                {
                    "N": "Sachin",
                    "T": "At long last... Someone to inherit my estate... and with it, my research."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Sachin",
                    "T": "Come, Kaveh. Come to me, my child..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Kaveh",
                    "T": "...How do you know my name? Who are you?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Sachin",
                    "T": "I am Sachin. Well, to be precise, I am but a fragment of Sachin's mind."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Sachin",
                    "T": "Fate is a curious thing... Seeing you reminds me of another I once met. But you are made of sterner stuff than he, more cognizant of the trials and tribulations of this world. It is you who are worthy to inherit all that I once owned."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Sachin",
                    "T": "We meet for the first time, children. But what I mean to say now is of utmost importance. So please, pay attention and bear witness."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Sachin",
                    "T": "You have all performed outstandingly in this Interdarshan Championship. The Akademiya has many rare talents among its ranks, and you are the creme of the creme."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Sachin",
                    "T": "But if I were to choose a successor, I would choose you, Kaveh. Not only because you were victorious, but also due to our similarities in character."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Kaveh",
                    "T": "...Me? Similar to you?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Sachin",
                    "T": "Why, yes. Both of us have the misfortune to be idealists — and that is the source of our misery."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Sachin",
                    "T": "Twenty-eight years ago, I came to the desert and lived there for eight full years. What do you think I saw there? Alas, endless strife and slaughter..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Sachin",
                    "T": "Conflict over water sources, robbing of merchant caravans, exploitation of the people... relentlessly, day after day. Beyond the Wall of Samiel lay a completely different world from the one I knew."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Sachin",
                    "T": "The things I witnessed there tormented me greatly. I wished desperately to find a way to save them."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Kaveh",
                    "T": "...So? Did you find a way?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Sachin",
                    "T": "As a Vahumana scholar, I tried to use Vahumana knowledge to find the answer."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Sachin",
                    "T": "I researched history and anthropology, performed countless experiments on human nature, and even sought out the scholars living deep in the desert who call themselves the \"Lost Darshan\"..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Sachin",
                    "T": "But in the end, I found that the answer I sought simply did not exist."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Sachin",
                    "T": "It was not possible to simply assign blame for these transgressions to any one party, for the sins are carved into humanity's very nature. Our nature begets conflict, and conflict begets destruction. This is the inexorable truth."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Sachin",
                    "T": "The aim of my research was to draw lessons from history, but what I discovered was that history offers no such guidance... Things can only ever go from bad to worse!"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Sachin",
                    "T": "After this realization, I could no longer see the meaning in anything that I had ever learned. Consumed by an overwhelming sense of emptiness, I could no longer bear to face life... and so I decided to bring my life to an end."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Sachin",
                    "T": "But before I went through with it, a strange twist of fate led me to come into the possession of this diadem, which has the ability to preserve part of one's consciousness. Into it, I placed my experiences, before requesting that the Akademiya manage my estate."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Alhaitham",
                    "T": "As I thought, the contract you signed with the Akademiya was, in essence, your will."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Alhaitham",
                    "T": "But if you'd given up hope on this world, why did you feel the need to do this?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Sachin",
                    "T": "I mentioned that I had performed a great many experiments concerning human nature... You may regard this as the very last experiment of them all."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Sachin",
                    "T": "The Akademiya has no shortage of genius talents, nurturing the brightest minds of every generation. And so, with a handsome reward to draw out the worthiest of individuals, my hope was that one day, I would find one who could untangle the mystery of human nature once and for all, and help to move the world onto a better path."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Alhaitham",
                    "T": "I see, so you desired a successor who was not only a genius, but who also understood the suffering of ordinary people. Such a person would have a clearer understanding of humanity, society, and the world."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Kaveh",
                    "T": "..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Alhaitham",
                    "T": "But did you ever consider that wealth numbs the human heart to the pain in the world? Even an idealist may be incapable of following through on your wishes after inheriting your wealth."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Sachin",
                    "T": "You are highly intelligent... Yet you are not the sort of person who would understand my line of thinking. To me, this is also part of the experiment — part of my investigation into human nature."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Sachin",
                    "T": "Whether my successor suffers as a consequence of my research or succumbs to an indulgence in pleasure-seeking, my research will have progressed."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Sachin",
                    "T": "I grieve the fundamental sickness of the world, I regret the unbearable weight of its history, and I lament the research that I failed to complete."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Sachin",
                    "T": "And this, Kaveh, my dear child... is why you will be of great utility to me."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Kaveh",
                    "T": "You're... you're absolutely certain that you want to give me everything you owned, for me to do with as I please?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Sachin",
                    "T": "I have faith in what I see in you. Now, wear the diadem, Kaveh, and complete the journey that I could not."
                }
            ]
        ]
    },
